TI  - The Structure of International bond risk differentials
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 107
EP  - 118
VL  - 17
IS  - 1
AB  - Many previous studies of the U.S. bond market have focused on the yield differential, the difference in yields on corporate and government bonds of the same maturity. These studies have generally found consistent and significant relationships between the yield differential and macroeconomic variables, with the yield differential being a positive function of the level of interest rates and the inflation rate and a negative function of the change in economic activity.
